ssinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-airlines-passengers-survived-because-abandoned-baggage-burning-plane-tokyo-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Starbucks%20app%20'traps'%20customers%20into%20a%20'vicious'%20spending%20cycle%2C%20consumer%20advocate%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Atlanta%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Starbucks%20Coffee%2C%20customer%20using%20mobile%20app%20to%20pay%20in%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659554f3ab6f2ebb11f86467%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStarbucks%20customers%20earn%20twice%20as%20many%20loyalty%20points%20if%20they%20pay%20for%20their%20orders%20on%20the%20app.%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Greenberg%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EStarbucks%20Cards%20make%20it%20nearly%20impossible%20for%20customers%20to%C2%A0%26quot%3Bzero%20out%26quot%3B%20their%20accounts%2C%20a%20consumer%20advocate%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECustomers%20can%20only%20reload%20money%20and%20leave%20tips%20in%20set%20amounts%20when%20they%20use%20their%20Starbucks%20Cards%20on%20the%20app.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Washington%20Consumer%20Protection%20Coalition%20said%20it%20was%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3BCatch-22%26quot%3B%20situation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Starbucks%20app%20traps%20customers%20in%20a%20cycle%20where%20they're%20%26quot%3Bperpetually%26quot%3B%20adding%20more%20money%20to%20their%20accounts%20because%20they%20can't%20use%20up%20their%20remaining%20balance%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1rO5rJr7N0GEFtcJUMaWiwYnz22fJlmck%2Fview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20consumer%20rights%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20customers%20earn%20twice%20as%20many%20loyalty%20points%20if%20they%20pay%20for%20their%20orders%20on%20the%20app%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20in%20advance%20or%20by%20scanning%20it%20in-store%20%E2%80%93%20using%20the%20coffee%20chain's%20digital%20Starbucks%20Card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Washington%20Consumer%20Protection%20Coalition%20says%20that%20certain%20features%20of%20the%20prepaid%20card%20mean%20that%20customers%20are%20trapped%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bvicious%20cycle%26quot%3B%20of%20spending%20more%20money%20at%20Starbucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20can%20only%20reload%20money%20to%20their%20Starbucks%20Card%20on%20the%20company's%20app%20in%20%245%20increments%2C%20with%20the%20minimum%20amount%20set%20at%20%2410.%20This%20means%20that%20customers%20usually%20aren't%20able%20to%20add%20just%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20they%20need%20to%20cover%20just%20one%20purchase%2C%20the%20Coalition%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20Catch-22%20traps%20customers%20in%20a%20cycle%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20have%20to%20add%20more%20money%20than%20they%20want%20to%20spend%2C%20and%20are%20left%20with%20odd%20amounts%20that%20they%20just%20can't%20use%20up.%20Plus%2C%20it's%20really%20hard%20to%20get%20your%20balance%20on%20the%20card%20down%20to%20zero%2C%20the%20complaint%20says.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20who%20know%20they'll%20have%20a%20small%20amount%20left%20on%20their%20card%20after%20they%20make%20their%20purchase%20could%20leave%20it%20as%20a%20tip%20to%20empty%20their%20account%20%E2%80%93%20but%20customers%20only%20have%20the%20option%20of%20leaving%20tips%20in%20pre-set%20amounts%20of%20%240.50%2C%20%241%2C%20%242%2C%20and%20%245%2C%20the%20group%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20also%20aren't%20able%20to%20split%20their%20payment%20across%20multiple%20payment%20methods%20when%20they%20order%20via%20the%20app%20and%20pay%20using%20their%20Rewards%20Card%20%E2%80%93%20meaning%20they%20can't%20use%20up%20the%20leftover%20balance%20on%20their%20card%20and%20then%20pay%20the%20remaining%20amount%20using%20a%20credit%20or%20debit%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20customer%20with%20%2410%20on%20their%20card%20who%20makes%20a%20%2411%20purchase%20has%20to%20reload%20another%20%2410%20onto%20their%20card%20to%20pay%2C%20leaving%20them%20with%20%249%20on%20their%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20practices%20trap%20consumers%20into%20perpetually%20reloading%20funds%20on%20their%20Starbucks%20Cards%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20use%20all%20remaining%20funds%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Coalition%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Coalition%20accused%20Starbucks%20of%20%26quot%3Bunfair%20and%20deceptive%20trade%20practices%26quot%3B%20that%20it%20alleged%20violated%20the%20Washington%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Coalition%20does%20note%2C%20however%2C%20that%20if%20customers%20reload%20their%20Starbucks%20Cards%20in-store%20they%20can%20choose%20a%20custom%20amount%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20at%20least%20%245.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20contacted%20Starbucks%20for%20comment.%20A%20Starbucks%20spokesperson%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F91004280%2Fcomplaint-starbucks-app-spending-cycle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFast%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20chain%20is%20committed%20to%20working%20with%20the%20State%20of%20Washington%20to%20ensure%20it%20remains%20in%20compliance%20with%20all%20state%20laws%20and%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks'%20app%20is%20booming%20business%20for%20the%20Seattle-based%20company%2C%20with%20many%20app%20users%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-record-revenues-tiktok-customizations-cold-drinks-food-earnings-coffee-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplacing%20bigger%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20paying%20extra%20to%20add%20modifications%20to%20their%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20app%20lets%20customers%20pay%20in%20advance%20and%