0the%20commanders%20and%20cadres%20of%20the%20movement%20to%20be%20martyred.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20expected%20to%20reach%20this%20age%2C%20so%20I%20am%20living%20on%20borrowed%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20AP%2C%20Arouri%20kept%20a%20low%20profile%20since%20October%207%2C%20when%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20terrorist%20attack%20on%20Israel%2C%20killing%20some%201%2C200%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-leader-killed-beirut-strike-said-living-on-borrowed-time-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704281848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659540c4ec62ab5daf8034bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-leader-killed-beirut-strike-said-living-on-borrowed-time-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Saleh%20Arouri%2C%20who%20was%20on%20Israel's%20hit%20list%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20a%20drone%20strike%20Tuesday.%20Last%20August%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20living%20on%20%26quot%3Bborrowed%20time.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%20Zitser)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-leader-killed-beirut-strike-said-living-on-borrowed-time-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Why%20Supreme%20Court%20Says%20Newspaper%20Reports%20Are%20Not%20Evidence%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20backed%20market%20regulator%20SEBI's%20clean%20chit%20to%20the%20Adani%20Group%20in%20the%20Hindenburg%20case%20and%20said%20the%20report%20by%20the%20OCCRP%20-%20an%20organisation%20funded%20by%20billionaire%20George%20Soros%2C%20among%20others%20-%20can't%20be%20the%20basis%20for%20doubting%20the%20capital%20markets%20regulator's%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20placing%20confidence%20in%20the%20investigation%20by%20SEBI%20or%20Securities%20and%20Exchanges%20Board%20of%20India%2C%20the%20bench%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20JB%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20dismissed%20the%20plea%20for%20a%20Special%20Investigation%20Team%20(SIT).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20rejected%20the%20petitioner's%20reliance%20on%20a%20news%20report%20by%20the%20OCCRP%20(Organised%20Crime%20and%20Corruption%20Reporting%20Project)%20without%20independent%20verification.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reliance%20on%20newspaper%20reports%20and%20third-party%20organisations%20to%20question%20the%20statutory%20regulator%20does%20not%20inspire%20confidence%20and%20is%20not%20to%20be%20viewed%20as%20conclusive%20evidence%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20originally%20ruled%20in%201988%20on%20whether%20newspaper%20articles%20could%20be%20used%20as%20evidence%20in%20a%20case.%20The%20case%20involved%20a%20murder%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMurder%20Most%20Foul%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20case%20was%20an%20appeal%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20by%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%2C%20convicted%20of%20murdering%20PN%20Gnanasambandam%2C%20acting%20manager%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20Bank%20in%20what%20was%20then%20called%20Madras.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20murder%20was%20a%20sensational%20one%2C%20which%20caught%20the%20imagination%20of%20the%20press%20in%20May%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20trial%20transcripts%2C%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20had%20stayed%20back%20in%20the%20Karnataka%20Bank%20on%20May%2020%20that%20year%2C%20working%20late%20with%20his%20acting%20manager%2C%20and%20having%20earlier%20gained%20the%20keys%20to%20the%20safety%20vault%2C%20strangled%20and%20stabbed%20him%20inside%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20proceeded%20to%20rob%20Rs%2014%20lakh%20from%20the%20vault%2C%20taking%20the%20cash%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bcoffee-coloured%20skybag%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20left%20the%20crime%20scene%20in%20an%20autorickshaw.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20managed%20to%20stump%20the%20police.%20He%20turned%20up%20to%20work%20as%20usual%20the%20next%20morning%20to%20allay%20suspicion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20initially%20drew%20a%20blank.%20But%2C%20in%20true%20movie%20style%2C%20a%20policeman%20made%20inquiries%20along%20with%20a%20plumber%20who%20used%20to%20sleep%20on%20the%20platform%20near%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plumber%20suggested%20that%20a%20local%20flower%20seller%2C%20Kanaka%2C%20may%20have%20some%20valuable%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20made%20a%20half-hearted%20attempt%20to%20find%20her%20and%2C%20learning%20that%20she%20was%20at%20her%20sister's%20house%20in%20Chennai's%20Vyasarpadi%2C%20gave%20up%20the%20trail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20Crime%20Branch%20and%20they%20found%20circumstantial%20evidence%20pointing%20to%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20as%20the%20prime%20suspect%20in%20the%20murder.%20It%20was%20now%20imperative%20for%20the%20police%20to%20find%20Kanaka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20police%20tracked%20her%20down%20and%20she%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20clinching%20factor%20as%20she%20claimed%20to%20have%20seen%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20leaving%20the%20bank%20around%209%20pm%20on%20the%20night%20of%20the%20murder%2C%20carrying%20a%20%26quot%3Bcoffee-coloured%20skybag%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Crime%20Branch%20then%20headed%20to%20Mangalore%20to%20catch%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20at%20his%20father%20Shivram%20Shetty's%20residence.%20But%20he%20had%20fled%20the%20city%20by%20train%20by%20the%20time%20the%20police%20arrived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20morning%20of%20May%2028%2C%201983%2C%20the%20police%20found%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20roaming%20around%20in%20Chennai's%20My%20Lady's%20Park.%20They%20took%20him%20to%20Mangalore%20on%20May%2030%2C%201983%2C%20to%20recover%20the%20loot%2C%20which%20was%20with%20his%20father.%20On%20the%20way%2C%20they%20found%20the%20father%20in%20a%20rickshaw%2C%20carrying%20boxes%20full%20of%20money.%20Both%20father%20and%20son%20were%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContradictory%20Newspaper%20Reports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police's%20case%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20collapse%20because%20of%20newspaper%20reports.%20The%20Indian%20Express%20Mangalore%20edition%20and%20three%20Tamil%20newspapers%20Malai%20Murasu%2C%20Makkal%20Kural%20and%20Dina%20Thanthi%20carried%20reports%20that%20the%20entire%20amount%20stolen%20from%20the%20bank%20had%20been%20recovered%20from%20Shivram%20Shetty's%20home%20in%20Mangalore%20and%20that%20both%20suspects%20had%20been%20taken%20into%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20prosecution%20had%20stated%20that%20the%20stolen%20cash%20was%20recovered%20in%20Madras.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20made%20the%20case%20even%20more%20compelling%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20on%20May%2030%2C%201983%2C%20then%20Chief%20Minister%20MG%20Ramachandran%20felicitated%20the%20key%20eyewitness%2C%20Kanaka%2C%20at%20a%20public%20function%20and%20rewarded%20her%20with%20Rs%205%2C000%20in%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20in%20a%20speech%2C%20cautioned%20newspapers%20%26quot%3Bagainst%20the%20danger%20of%20conjectural%20reporting%20of%20such%20crimes%20during%20investigation%2C%20based%20on%20rumours%20unrelated%20to%20facts%2C%20which%20would%20not%20only%20prejudice%20the%20case%20but%20also%20sometimes%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20the%20offender%20to%20escape%26quot%3B.%20He%20said%20that%20rumours%20were%20bound%20to%20sidetrack%20and%20mislead%20the%20public%20and%20even%20police%20officers%20concerned%20with%20solving%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20discrepancy%20was%20brought%20on%20record%20by%20Laxmi%20Raj%20Shetty%20and%20his%20father%20Shivram%20Shetty%20in%20the%20Madras%20High%20Court%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3B%20they%20argued%20that%20the%20police%20were%20lying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20AP%20Sen%20categorically%20rejected%20the%20pleas%20of%20the%20Shettys%2C%20although%20the%20death%20sentence%20was%20converted%20to%20life%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20take%20judicial%20notice%20of%20the%20facts%20stated%20in%20a%20news%20item%20being%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20hearsay%20secondary%20evidence%20unless%20proved%20by%20evidence%20aliunde.%20A%20report%20in%20a%20newspaper%20is%20only%20hearsay%20evidence.%20A%20newspaper%20is%20not%20one%20of%20the%20documents%20referred%20to%20in%20s.%2078(2)%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20by%20which%20an%20allegation%20of%20fact%20can%20be%20proved.%20The%20presumption%20of%20genuineness%20attached%20under%20Section%2081%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20to%20a%20newspaper%20report%20cannot%20be%20treated%20as%20proved%20of%20the%20facts%20reported%20therein.%26quot%3B%20-%20observed%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20judgment%20by%20a%20single%20judge%20was%20later%20upheld%20by%20a%20Bench%20comprising%20Justice%20S%20Ratnavel%20Pandian%2C%20Justice%20RM%20Sahai%2C%20and%20Justice%20Dr%20AS%20Anand%20in%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Sandhya%20Ravishankar%20is%20a%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704281820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fc5p4n3lg_supreme-court-premises_625x300_22_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnewspaper-reports-not-proof-1994-supreme-court-precedent-in-hindenburg-case-4792592%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20backed%20market%20regulator%20SEBI's%20clean%20chit%20to%20the%20Adani%20Group%20in%20th