tion%20but%20...'%3A%20Chouhan%20turns%20emotional%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704273339000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106511938%2Cimgsize-36388.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsometimes-one-waits-for-coronation-but-ends-up-in-exile-ex-mp-cm-shivraj-chouhan-turns-emotional%2Farticleshow%2F106511873.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20turned%20emotional%20while%20addressing%20his%20supporters%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20saying%20that%20sometimes%20one%20waits%20for%20%26quot%3Brajtilak%26quot%3B%20(coronation)%20but%20ends%20up%20in%20%26quot%3Bvanvas%26quot%3B%20(exile).Chouhan%2C%20who%20was%20addressing%20a%20gathering%20in%20Shahganj%20town%20under%20his%20Budhni%20assembly%20seat%20on%20January%202%2C%20promised%20that%20he%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20among%20the%20people%2C%20especially%20his%20sisters.The%20four-time%20chief%20minister%2C%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20BJP's%20landslide%20victory%20in%20the%20recent%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20elections%2C%20had%20to%20make%20way%20for%20Mohan%20Yadav%20last%20month%20after%20the%20party%20decided%20to%20go%20for%20a%20new%20line%20of%20leadership%20in%20the%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsometimes-one-waits-for-coronation-but-ends-up-in-exile-ex-mp-cm-shivraj-chouhan-turns-emotional%2Farticleshow%2F106511873.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20Political%20Repression%20and%20Economic%20Crisis%2C%20Bangladesh%20is%20Set%20for%20a%20One-Sided%20Election%20on%20Jan%207%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03144455%2FEffect-52.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20period%20of%20economic%20boom%20and%20political%20tranquility.%20There%20are%20shiny%20new%20buildings%2C%20expressways%2C%20and%20bridges.%20Shopping%20malls%20abound%20with%20imported%20luxury%20brands.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20dark%20spots%20%E2%80%93inequality%20is%20rising%2C%20and%20dissent%20is%20stifled.%20But%20these%20are%20ignored%20in%20the%20superficially%20laudatory%20articles%20in%20the%20foreign%20media.%20Meanwhile%2C%20foreign%20financiers%20lend%20to%20the%20country%20willingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%2C%20of%20course%2C%20things%20change.%20And%20they%20change%20rather%20quickly.%20All%20those%20things%20that%20were%20glossed%20over%20previously%20suddenly%20loom%20large.%20Turns%20out%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20banks%20are%20saddled%20with%20bad%20loans%20issued%20to%20politically%20connected%20cronies%20and%20crooks.%20The%20currency%20tanks.%20Inflation%20soars.%20With%20peaceful%20democratic%20avenues%20closed%2C%20a%20spasm%20of%20violence%20ensues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20persistent%20current%20account%20deficit%2C%20banking%20sector%20woes%2C%20and%20authoritarian%20politics%20make%20for%20a%20volatile%20cocktail%20that%20is%20redolent%20of%20Southeast%20Asia%20of%20the%20mid-1990s%20%E2%80%93%20but%20as%20things%20stand%2C%20they%20also%20describe%20a%20Bangladesh%20of%20the%20mid-2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20consider%20each%20of%20these%20elements%20in%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Bangladesh%20has%20become%20a%20capital%20importer%2C%20running%20a%20current%20account%20deficit%20even%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20And%2C%20according%20to%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20(IMF%E2%80%99s)%20latest%20assessment%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economy%2C%20the%20deficit%20is%20likely%20to%20persist%20well%20into%20the%20late%202020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20nation%E2%80%99s%20current%20account%20reflects%20the%20difference%20between%20its%20aggregate%20savings%20and%20investment%2C%20with%20a%20deficit%20signifying%20inadequate%20savings%20to%20meet%20its%20investment%20needs.%20With%20around%2030%25%20of%20GDP%20saved%2C%20the%20savings%20rate%20in%20Bangladesh%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20low%20%E2%80%93%20by%20way%20of%20comparison%2C%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20savings%20rate%20has%20tended%20to%20be%20around%2015%25%20of%20GDP.%20Rather%2C%20as%20Chart%201%20shows%2C%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20current%20account%20deficit%20reflects%20a%20strong%20investment%20boom%20before%20the%20pandemic%20that%20is%20set%20to%20resume%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22929%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2.jpg%20929w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2-300x186.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691395%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22575%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20Chart%202%20shows%20that%20while%20private%20investment%20is%20set%20to%20recover%20to%20the%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20relative%20to%20GDP%2C%20shaking%20off%20recent%20woes%2C%20public%20investment%20is%20projected%20to%20scale%20new%20heights%20in%20the%20medium%20term.%20Of%20course%2C%20in%20and%20of%20itself%2C%20this%20is%20very%20sensible.%20Bangladesh%20is%20a%20developing%20country%20desperately%20in%20need%20of%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20roads%2C%20railways%2C%20electricity%20generation%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20There%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20financing%20some%20of%20these%20projects%20from%20external%20sources%2C%20provided%20the%20projects%20are%20well%20governed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20elements%20to%20this.%20First%2C%20financing%20of%20many%20of%20these%20projects%20is%20quite%20one-sided%20against%20Bangladeshi%20taxpayers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froadtodemocracy.com%2F2023%2F03%2F20%2Fadani-group-awami-league-nexus%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20power%20purchase%20agreement%20with%20the%20Adani%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20a%20particularly%20egregious%2C%20but%20far%20from%20the%20only%2C%20example.%20Second%2C%20these%20projects%20are%20usually%20implemented%20with%20woeful%20management%2C%20resulting%20in%20significant%20cost%20overruns.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbdnews24.com%2Feconomy%2Fbangladesh-infrastructure-is-worlds-costliest-says-world-bank%5C%22%3Einfrastructure%20projects%20were%20among%20the%20costliest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20persistent%20current%20account%20deficit%20may%20well%20have%20an%20upside%20to%20it%2C%20at%20least%20theoretically%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20positive%20about%20a%20wobbly%20banking%20sector.%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20banking%20sector%20is%20saddled%20with%20non-performing%20loans%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20borrower%20has%20failed%20to%20make%20interest%20or%20principal%20payments%20for%20an%20extended%20period.%20Chart%203%20shows%20that%20the%20problem%20is%20particularly%20acute%20in%20the%20state-owned%20banks%2C%20which%20are%20also%20not%20well%20capitalised%20(Chart%204)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20they%20are%20not%20well%20placed%20to%20cover%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20their%20lending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22951%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4.jpg%20951w%2C%20ht