et%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5.jpg%20857w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5-300x164.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691399%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%E2%80%99s%20turn%20towards%20a%20dictatorship%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20third%20consecutive%20one-sided%20election%20on%20January%207%20%E2%80%93%20the%20opposition%20parties%20are%20boycotting%20the%20election%20in%20light%20of%20their%20past%20experience%20as%20well%20as%20the%20fact%20that%20over%2020%2C000%20of%20their%20members%20have%20been%20interned%20since%20late%20October%20through%20a%20draconian%20crackdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20may%20look%20unassailable%20politically.%20But%20so%20did%20President%20Suharto%20of%20Indonesia%20in%201996.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20nostrum%20pushed%20by%20authoritarian%20leaders%20that%20they%20can%20make%20the%20tough%20decisions%20needed%20to%20address%20economic%20challenges%2C%20experiences%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20(and%20indeed%20in%20many%20other%20countries%20around%20the%20world)%20suggest%20that%20authoritarian%20regimes%20with%20poorly%20governed%20banking%20sectors%20and%20mega%20projects%20often%20end%20up%20in%20significant%20political%20and%20economic%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20making%20tough%20decisions%20and%20taking%20on%20the%20vested%20interests%2C%20authoritarian%20regimes%20relied%20on%20the%20very%20same%20vested%20interests%20for%20their%20survival.%20The%20resulting%20cronyism%20only%20exacerbated%20the%20crisis%2C%20not%20resolved%20it.%20In%20Thailand%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Asian%20Financial%20Crisis%20of%201997%20was%20followed%20by%20years%20of%20political%20conflict%20and%20economic%20stagnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%2C%20of%20course%2C%20has%20been%20experiencing%20considerable%20economic%20difficulty%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20with%20the%20taka%20depreciating%20by%20over%2040%25%20against%20the%20US%20dollar%20despite%20the%20central%20bank%20burning%20through%20about%20half%20of%20its%20international%20reserves%20while%20inflation%20remained%20at%20double%20digits.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20noxious%20politics%20and%20unsound%20economic%20fundamentals%20make%20for%20a%20very%20combustible%20brew%20that%20could%20spill%20over%20beyond%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJyoti%20Rahman%20is%20a%20Bangladeshi%20economist.%20His%20analyses%20are%20archived%20at%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjrahman.substack.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fjrahman.substack.com%2F%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20he%20can%20be%20contacted%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3AJyoti.rahman%40gmail.com%5C%22%3EJyoti.rahman%40gmail.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704273025000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03144455%2FEffect-52.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fdespite-political-repression-economic-crisis-bangladesh-is-set-for-a-one-sided-election-on-jan-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20opposition%20parties%20boycotting%20the%20election%20and%20mass%20arrests%2C%20Bangladesh's%20turn%20towards%20a%20dictatorship%20under%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20third%20consecutive%20one-sided%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fdespite-political-repression-economic-crisis-bangladesh-is-set-for-a-one-sided-election-on-jan-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saleh%20al%20Arouri%3A%20Who%20was%20the%20deputy%20Hamas%20leader%20killed%20in%20Beirut%20explosion%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704272880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm