20third-hottest%20May%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20years%20between%202014%20and%202023%20have%20been%20the%20ten%20warmest%20on%20record%20according%20to%20NASA%20and%20NOAA.%20The%20year%202016%2C%20which%20like%202023%20included%20the%20influence%20of%20a%20strong%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%2C%20was%20the%20warmest%20year%20on%20Earth%20at%20its%20conclusion.%20It%20was%20about%20matched%20by%202020%20and%20both%20will%20now%20be%20overtaken%20by%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20fluctuating%20temperatures%20and%20very%20hot%2C%20very%20dry%20or%20very%20cold%20days%20are%20a%20normal%20phenomenon%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Ftopics%2F5438%2Fweather-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20weather%20events%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20become%20more%20frequent%20and%20severe%20due%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Ftopics%2F1148%2Fglobal-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Overall%2C%20a%20higher%20concentration%20of%20CO%E2%82%82%20and%20other%20climate%20gases%20in%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%20has%20led%20to%20rising%20average%20global%20temperatures%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.nasa.gov%2Fscientific-consensus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escientific%20consensus%20has%20found.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%202023%20Expected%20to%20Be%20Hottest%20Year%20on%20Record%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F18267%2Faverage-global-temperature-records%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%202023%20Expected%20to%20Be%20Hottest%20Year%20on%20Record%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.statcdn.com%2FInfographic%2Fimages%2Fnormal%2F18267.jpeg%5C%22%20